Wind River SBC8548e Board Support Package
=========================================

Building
--------

Use the following steps to configure a platform project for this BSP with
Wind River Linux 8:

	$ configure --enable-board=wrs-sbc8548 \
		--enable-rootfs=glibc_std \
		--enable-kernel=standard \
		--with-layer=/path/to/wrl-sbc8548-bsp

Some useful templates to consider adding for on-target debug and analysis
are:

	--with-template=feature/analysis
	--with-template=feature/debug
	--with-template=feature/lttng

Then build the platform with:

	$ make fs

-or-

	$ make -C build linux-windriver

to build just a kernel.
